The paper studies the outcome of a strategic choice made by participants in a matching market, which is a classic topic in game theory (cs.GT). The study also involves experimental results, which suggests a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the effect of selfish behavior on social welfare, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the deferred acceptance algorithm, which is a well-known mechanism design tool in economics (cs.EC).
